<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,359,1108,1135]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,1108,1135]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">Podothrips</emphasis>
Hood
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1108,1314]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">
There are 31 species listed in this genus (ThripsWiki 2020), with identification keys provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritchie, J. M." box="[1175,1329,1146,1170]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" pagination="261 - 282" refId="ref2827" refString="Ritchie, J. M. (1974) A revision of the grass-living genus Podothrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae). Journal of Entomology, B, 43, 261 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1975. tb 00135. x" type="journal article" year="1974">Ritchie (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Dang, L. - H. &amp; Zhao, L. &amp; Wang, X. &amp; Qiao, G. - X." pageId="2" pageNumber="198" pagination="41 - 49" refId="ref2575" refString="Dang, L. - H., Zhao, L. Wang, X. &amp; Qiao, G. - X. (2019) Review of Podothrips from China (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripidae), with one new species and three new records. Zookeys, 882, 41 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 882.39029" type="journal article" year="2019">
Dang 
<emphasis box="[151,197,1182,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 10 species recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[611,666,1182,1206]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tyagi, K. &amp; Kumar, V." box="[679,911,1182,1206]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" pagination="64 - 98" refId="ref2941" refString="Tyagi, K. &amp; Kumar, V. (2016) Thrips (Insecta: Thysanoptera) of India: An Updated Checklist. Halteres, 7, 64 - 98." type="journal article" year="2016">Tyagi &amp; Kumar 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Seshadri, A. &amp; Ananthakrishnan, T. N." box="[928,1328,1181,1206]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" pagination="210 - 226" refId="ref2880" refString="Seshadri, A. &amp; Ananthakrishnan, T. N. (1954) Some new Indian Thysanoptera - 1. Indian Journal of Entomology, 16, 210 - 226." type="journal article" year="1954">Seshadri and Ananthakrishnan (1954)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seshadri &amp; Ananthakrishnan" authorityYear="1954" box="[151,353,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Podothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[151,353,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">Podothrips bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from grasses in 
<collectingCountry box="[528,583,1218,1242]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">India</collectingCountry>
, and this species has been reported subsequently from 
<collectingCountry box="[1165,1229,1218,1242]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dang, L. - H. &amp; Zhao, L. &amp; Wang, X. &amp; Qiao, G. - X." box="[1243,1422,1218,1242]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" pagination="41 - 49" refId="ref2575" refString="Dang, L. - H., Zhao, L. Wang, X. &amp; Qiao, G. - X. (2019) Review of Podothrips from China (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripidae), with one new species and three new records. Zookeys, 882, 41 - 49. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 882.39029" type="journal article" year="2019">
Dang 
<emphasis box="[1308,1355,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). The number of sense cones on antennal segment IV has been used to distinguish species in this genus, but we have recognised variation in these structures amongst specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[788,845,1290,1314]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">India</collectingCountry>
, as discussed below.
</paragraph>
